2. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper uses a Linear Quadratic Minimum Time control problem to generate motion primitives, which falls under the domain of systems and control. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses a graph-search algorithm to explore the state space, which can be considered a form of machine learning. 
4. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): Although not directly related to computer vision, the paper does deal with obstacle avoidance, which can be considered a form of perception. 
5. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes an approach for generating dynamically feasible trajectories, which can be considered a form of artificial intelligence.
